<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-03T21:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-03T21:41:00-05:00" n="1215" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1215">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/92.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-03T20:00:00-06:41">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Since sending my June 3, 2 p.m., re new decree collection customs
                            Charges, I have conferred with Sr. F. Villareal, Secretary
                            Communications of Constitutionalists and he informs me that decree
                            applies only to export Charges, bar Charges, and oil production taxes,
                            and will not be applied to import duties. Rule is based on theory that
                            all exports are sold abroad on gold basis.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>